We reiterated the following recommendations:

require the Municipal Engineer and MPDO to provide and to take full responsibility of the preparation of the required reports and strictly observe the timely submission of the same to the Audit Team;
advice concerned officials to religiously adopt and comply with the full disclosure policy of the state on matters of public interest as clearly professed and embodied in the Constitution;
direct the Municipal Engineer to strictly comply with the required posting of information and publicity on programs/projects/activities of government agencies and inform the Audit Team within 10 days after the award of the projects or before the start of the programs/projects/activities that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted at the project sites; and
refrain from incurring expenses in violation of the afore-cited Circular as this shall be disallowed in audit and subject to administrative disciplinary action provided under penalty clause of the same COA Circular.

We reiterated the following:

The Inventory Committee shall conduct semestral physical inventory of supplies and prepare the corresponding RPCI, and reconcile the same with the property and accounting records. It shall then be submitted to the Auditor pursuant to Section 124, Volume I of NGAS Manual for LGUs; 

The General Services Office thru its supply and property officer prepares and maintains SCs for each type of supplies and materials while its Accounting Office maintains SLCs for each supplies and materials acquired and issued to support the year-end balances of the supplies and materials inventory and expense accounts in the financial statements;

The supply and property officer consolidates weekly/monthly the RIS for which supplies and materials were issued using the SSMI. Submit the SSMI supported by RIS to the Accountant for recording pursuant to Section 121, Volume I of NGAS Manual for LGUs; and

The property officer makes a revisit and review of the LGU’s existing policies and procedures with regards to inventory process, which must be followed as a control procedure of inventory as required and provided under Section 122, Volume I of NGAS Manual for LGUs.

