15.9	We recommended that:
The Inventory Committee shall conduct semestral physical inventory of supplies and prepare the corresponding RPCI, and reconcile the same with the property and accounting records. It shall then be submitted to the Auditor pursuant to Section 124, Volume I of NGAS Manual for LGUs;
The General Services Office thru its Supply and Property Officer prepares and maintains SCs for each type of supplies and materials while its Accounting Office maintains SLCs for each supplies and materials acquired and issued to support the year-end balances of the supplies and materials inventory and expense accounts in the financial statements;
The Supply and Property Officer consolidates weekly/monthly the RIS for which supplies and materials were issued using the SSMI. Submit the SSMI supported by RIS to the Accountant for recording pursuant to Section 121, Volume I of NGAS Manual for LGUs; and
The Property Officer makes a revisit and review of the LGU’s existing policies and procedures with regards to inventory process, which must be followed as a control procedure of inventory as required and provided under Section 122, Volume 1 of NGAS Manual for LGUs.

We recommended that:

the Supply Officer be required that stock cards be maintained and keep up-to-date for each item particularly drugs and medicines as well as Medical, Dental and Laboratory Supplies;
the Municipal Accounting Office record all purchases to its corresponding inventory account classification and to adjust this account for whatever consumption on the basis of Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI), duly supported with the original copy of Requisition Issue Slip (RIS).

We recommended that Management:

Require the Municipal Accountant, Municipal Engineer and the General Services Officer to comply to the Accounting and Reporting Procedures and to their respective duties and responsibilities provided in Items V and VII of COA Circular No. 2017-008 dated November 25, 2017, respectively;

Submit a duly accomplished copy of Annexes A to E to the Audit Team for evaluation and verification;

Direct the Municipal Engineer to prepare specific estimated useful life for each depreciable components of the Local Road Network based on LGU’s experience on the life of its PPE, copy furnished the Audit Team;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to comply to the transitory period of recognizing the Local Road Network in the books of accounts, effect the corresponding depreciation and make necessary disclosure in the Notes to the Financial Statements; and

In the existing Inventory Committee, the inclusion of a representative from the Engineering Department is recommended to facilitate identification and evaluation of the technical aspect of the projects.

