advice concerned officials to religiously adopt and comply with the full disclosure policy of the state on matters of public interest as clearly professed and embodied in the Constitution;
direct the Municipal Engineer to strictly comply with the required posting of information and publicity on programs/projects/activities of government agencies and inform the Audit Team within 10 days after the award of the projects or before the start of the programs/projects/activities that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted at the project sites; and
refrain from incurring expenses in violation of the afore-cited Circular as this shall be disallowed in audit.

We  recommended that the Municipal Accountant  apply accounting standards and method of recording supplies and materials consistently cognizant of the accrual basis of accounting required under PPSAS 12; 

We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant coordinate with the General Services Department for the setting up of internal control measures that will minimize the discrepancy between the Accounting records and actual inventory on hand, holding the designated supply officers accountable for the discrepancy.

Likewise, we recommended that the Supply Officer update the supply ledger cards and reconcile the same with the accounting records as often as necessary, and  conduct annual inventory of supplies, drugs and medicine, and other office supplies and materials.

